INSERT INTO `knowledge_versions` VALUES (5,3,1,'<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Domain Lifecycle Overview<br><br>it is important to understand that a domain does not immediately become available to the public the moment it expires. It follows a specific timeline:</p><ul data-path-to-node=\"7\"><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Active Status:</b> The domain is functional and points to the intended resources.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Auto-Renew Period (0–45 Days post-expiry):</b> Most registrars offer a \"Grace Period\" where the domain is deactivated (website/email stops working), but the owner can still renew at the standard price.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Redemption Grace Period (30 Days following Grace Period):</b> The domain is held by the registry. Renewal is still possible but usually requires a heavy \"Redemption Fee\" (often $100+).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pending Delete (5 Days):</b> The domain cannot be recovered. It is waiting to be released back to the general public for registration.</p></li></ul>','hari','2026-01-01 12:47:07'),(6,3,2,'<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Domain Lifecycle Overview<br><br>it is important to understand that a domain does not immediately become available to the public the moment it expires. It follows a specific timeline:</p><ul data-path-to-node=\"7\"><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Active Status:</b> The domain is functional and points to the intended resources.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Auto-Renew Period (0–45 Days post-expiry):</b> Most registrars offer a \"Grace Period\" where the domain is deactivated (website/email stops working), but the owner can still renew at the standard price.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Redemption Grace Period (30 Days following Grace Period):</b> The domain is held by the registry. Renewal is still possible but usually requires a heavy \"Redemption Fee\" (often $100+).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pending Delete (5 Days):</b> The domain cannot be recovered. It is waiting to be released back to the general public for registration.</p></li></ul>','hari','2026-01-02 05:54:39'),(7,3,3,'<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Domain Lifecycle Overview<br><br>it is important to understand that a domain does not immediately become available to the public the moment it expires. It follows a specific timeline:</p><ul data-path-to-node=\"7\"><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Active Status:</b> The domain is functional and points to the intended resources.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Auto-Renew Period (0–45 Days post-expiry):</b> Most registrars offer a \"Grace Period\" where the domain is deactivated (website/email stops working), but the owner can still renew at the standard price.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Redemption Grace Period (30 Days following Grace Period):</b> The domain is held by the registry. Renewal is still possible but usually requires a heavy \"Redemption Fee\" (often $100+).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pending Delete (5 Days):</b> The domain cannot be recovered. It is waiting to be released back to the general public for registration.</p></li></ul>','admin','2026-01-02 09:46:41'),(8,3,4,'<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Domain Lifecycle Overview<br><br>it is important to understand that a domain does not immediately become available to the public the moment it expires. It follows a specific timeline:</p><ul data-path-to-node=\"7\"><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Active Status:</b> The domain is functional and points to the intended resources.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Auto-Renew Period (0–45 Days post-expiry):</b> Most registrars offer a \"Grace Period\" where the domain is deactivated (website/email stops working), but the owner can still renew at the standard price.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Redemption Grace Period (30 Days following Grace Period):</b> The domain is held by the registry. Renewal is still possible but usually requires a heavy \"Redemption Fee\" (often $100+).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><b data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pending Delete (5 Days):</b> The domain cannot be recovered. It is waiting to be released back to the general public for registration.</p></li></ul>','admin','2026-01-02 13:38:29'),(11,6,1,'<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-e1389ba2-7fff-7ee2-7614-54d5cc3aec7e\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3218586921691895;margin-right: 5.7431640625pt;text-indent: -1.240997314453125pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.240997314453125pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Acceptable Use Policy (AUP) – Server Hosting &amp; Email</span><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Hosting Packages</span><span style=\"font-size: 17pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-left: 1.144500732421875pt;margin-top:13.318359375pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">1.Email storage cannot exceed 50% of your hosting disk space</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-left: 0.30449676513671875pt;margin-top:11.82049560546875pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">2.Email storage must not exceed 10 GB, even if within the 50% limit</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-left: 0.44100189208984375pt;margin-top:11.82049560546875pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">3.Mailboxes cannot be used as long-term storage or archive dumping</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-left: 0.13649749755859375pt;margin-top:11.82049560546875pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">4.Zero tolerance for spam — no unsolicited bulk or commercial emails</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-left: 0.44100189208984375pt;margin-top:11.82049560546875pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">5.Any email activity must comply with the U.S. CAN-SPAM Act</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-left: 0.3990020751953125pt;margin-top:11.82049560546875pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">6.You must not engage in any illegal or harmful email activity</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:2.291842317581177;margin-left: 0.4304962158203125pt;margin-right: 76.41464233398438pt;text-indent: 0.0630035400390625pt;margin-top:11.82049560546875pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">7.Hosting is strictly for website files, active emails, and site content Not allowed:</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">8.Storing large media, backups, or files unrelated to your website</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-left: 0.44100189208984375pt;margin-top:2.266845703125pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: